-- Monti Says Italy Won’t Need Backstop Aid, Deutschlandradio Says
-- B y   R a i n e r   B u e r g i n
-- 2012-06-13T07:35:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-13/monti-says-italy-won-t-need-backstop-aid-deutschlandradio-says.html
Italian Prime Minister  Mario Monti 
said his country won’t need aid from the euro region’s financial
backstops, Germany’s  Deutschlandradio Kultur  reported, citing an
interview.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rainer Buergin in Berlin at 
